The `CreateFormFile(string fileName, string content)` helper is duplicated across two test files: it appears in `TestProject.Tests/Services/FileServiceTests.cs` AND in `TestProject.Tests/Controllers/FilesControllerTests.cs` (after task-25 extracts FakeFileService, the helper likely travels with it into `FakeFileService.cs`, OR remains in `FilesControllerTests.cs` — verify by searching for `CreateFormFile` before starting). The two implementations are byte-identical. Create a shared static utility class `TestProject.Tests/TestHelpers/FormFileFactory.cs` (namespace `TestProject.Tests.TestHelpers`) with a single `public static IFormFile CreateFormFile(string fileName, string content)` method containing the existing implementation. Replace both duplicated copies with calls to the shared helper: add `using TestProject.Tests.TestHelpers;` to each consuming file and replace local `CreateFormFile(...)` calls with `FormFileFactory.CreateFormFile(...)` (or keep the local name as a thin forwarding wrapper if that minimizes diff — either is fine, but prefer direct calls). Remove the duplicated private static methods. Do NOT change any test assertions or behavior. Verification: `dotnet build TestProject.sln`; `dotnet test TestProject.Tests/TestProject.Tests.csproj` passes.

